404040; font-size: 16px; line-height: 26px; margin: 0 0 20px 0;">A few week=
s ago I got a call from my sister and she informed me she was in Rwanda. &#=
8220;Rwanda?&#8221; I anxiously asked. From the tone of my voice, she could=
 tell that I was scared. And she knew why I was scared. Rwanda, at least in=
 the West, is associated with genocide. You don&#8217;t want to get a call =
from your sister and have the first words come out of her mouth immediately=
 conjure images of genocide.</p><p style=3D"color: #404040; font-size: 16px=
; line-height: 26px; margin: 0 0 20px 0;">She quickly assuaged my fears. Rw=
anda, she informed me, was now like the &#8220;Singapore of Africa.&#8221; =
Since 1994, under the leadership of President Paul Kagame, the country has =
experienced rapid economic development and stabilization. It&#8217;s where =
my sister goes on the continent to get banking business done quickly. Its t=
ourism economy has rebounded. And, as the story above notes, it&#8217;s dev=
eloped somewhat of a playbook for developing countries in increasing health=
care availability and lengthening lifespans.</p><p style=3D"color: #404040;=
 font-size: 16px; line-height: 26px; margin: 0 0 20px 0;">The government, t=
o be certain, does face criticism. But overall, the country is starting to =
become known more forward thinking policies on healthcare, technology, and =
gender equality and less known for its darkest moment.</p><p style=3D"color=
: #404040; font-size: 16px; line-height: 26px; margin: 0 0 20px 0;"><span>(=
